238943991687415916.Text: The Siege of the Skaal Village

3080322243563920150.Text: Creatures are attacking the Skaal village. I should go outside and help to defend these people.

32375259281012611949.Text: The werewolves attacking the Skaal Village have been defeated.

1903073041534414041.Text: I have been told that at least one werewolf was seen going into the Greathall. I should go make sure that those inside are safe.

1121018336152146536.Text: The werewolves inside the Greathall are defeated. The Skaal Guard that was inside is dead. Heart-Fang, however, is nowhere to be found.

7814259088582488.Text: Residents of the Skaal Village have suggested I speak with Korst Wind-Eye, who has returned.

130092451299027628.Text: Wind-Eye tells me that during the battle with the werewolves, he believes I was infected by one of them. A Cure Disease spell will rid me of the affliction, but if I do not do this within three days, I may become a werewolf myself. Until I have been cured, Wind-Eye cannot allow me to be a part of the Skaal community.

13097451116868925.Text: I have lived with the Lycanthropy disease too long, and the Skaal believe I am a werewolf. I am not welcome among them until I have found a cure.

1367439612882624324.Text: I have been cured of the Lycanthropy disease, and may once again be a part of the Skaal. I have been named Blodskaal, a blood friend to the village. They will allow me to use Rigmor Halfhand's former house as my own.

282943155815625478.Text: I have cured myself of Lycanthropy, and have been welcomed back by the Skaal. I have been named Blodskaal, a blood friend to the village. They will allow me to use Rigmor Half-Hand's former house as my own.
